Mattia De Sciglio has signed an extension to his Juventus contract which will keep him at the club until 2025, the Serie A side announced on Thursday. Italyâ€™s De Sciglio played 29 times for Juve in all competitions last season after returning from a loan at Lyon. The full-back, 29, has been at the Turin giants since 2017, winning three league titles and an Italian Cup. Last year, Juve finished fourth in Serie A, failing to win a trophy for the first time since 2010. De Sciglio has represented his country 40 times.